//Advisory Expert advice on pot plants in month of March 20-03-2019 Punjab Agricultural University, Ludhiana Advisory The information about pot plants is given below
-Best time for the propagation, manuring and repotting of shade loving and other pot plants like Dracaena, Pedilanthus, Alocasia, Chlorophytum, Ferns, Rhoeo etc. -The plants which had been growing in a pot for more than 3-4 years should be taken out from the pot, if required divided/multiplied into two or more than two parts of the each (depending upon their size and health) and then replant the same in pots by using fresh and rich potting mixture. -This will enhance their physical look.
Special Advisories for Horticulture operations 19-03-2019 Punjab Agricultural University, Ludhiana Advisory The information about Horticulture operations is given below: 1. The evergreen fruit plants like citrus, mango, litchi, guava, loquat and ber may be planted in the field.
2. The young as well as the old trees should be irrigated regularly and more frequently as they put forth new growth/ flushes. The young plants should be provided with stakes for upright and straight growth. To litchi trees, apply irrigation after the fruit set and continue watering at 3 weeks intervals. Tograpevines, one irrigation is needed during the first week of March.
3. The lower portion of the exposed trunks should be white-washed with a thick lime solution towards the end of this month.
4. For rejuvenation of senile guava trees, head back such trees at 1.5m from the ground level leaving 2-3 primary scaffolds and apply Bordeaux Paste on the cut ends.
5. For checking foot rot in citrus, drench the soil around basin of the tree and free trunk with Sodium hypochlorite 5% @ 50ml tree in 10 litres of water.
6. Ethephon 400 ppm at Colour break stage (250 ml in 300 litres of water in first week of March) advances ripening by two weeks in Umran and produces attractive, uniform, better quality and deep golden yellow with chocolate tinge coloured fruit. The peak season for harvesting of ber in Punjab is mid-March to mid-April.
7. To check the insect pests of citrus especially psylla and aphids, spray 200 ml Crocodile/Confidor 17.8 SL or 160g Actara/Dotara 25 WG (thiamethoxam) 500 litres of water on spring flush. For the control of withertip or die-back in citrus, spray Bordeaux mixture 2:2:250 before the flower opening.
